---
title: Argentine-Spiced Steak with Couscous Salad & Cilantro-Scallion Chimichurri
description: Argentina is renowned for incredible steaks, so it goes without saying that they know how to dress them up right. Chimichurri is an Argentinian herb sauce traditionally made with green herbs, vinegar, garlic, and plenty of olive oil. Here we used mellow scallion greens and fresh cilantro for vibrancy. Served over cumin-scented steak, it's a killer combination.
